<h2>The weather in February 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
Temperatures in February 2020 were exceptionally above the 1981-2010 average over almost all of Europe (Figure 8). The European-average temperature was 3.9&deg;C warmer than the average February temperature for 1981-2010 (Figure 7). Only in Ireland, Scotland, and parts of Scandinavia temperatures were around the 1981-2010 average.
